The paper deals with network formation games, which are a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also discusses the concept of inequality in these games, which is a topic of interest in social choice theory (cs.SI) and social network analysis (cs.SOC). The paper uses mathematical analysis to derive upper bounds on a quantity called the Nash Inequality Ratio, which is related to optimization and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the relationship between efficiency and inequality, which is a topic of interest in information theory (cs.IT).
